1
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:15,200
How did you ambush in the museum?

2
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:17,319
Xue Li went missing.

3
00:01:17,599 --> 00:01:20,200
It was Jiang Xun who found him dead in the corridor.

4
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:23,239
Even the museum curator didn't know about the corridor.

5
00:01:23,439 --> 00:01:24,599
How did she know?

6
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,400
Obviously, she's not telling the truth.

7
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,040
I suspect she's in cahoots with the spy.

8
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:30,120
They're working together to put on this act.

9
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,319
A thief crying 'stop thief'.

10
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,480
Where is Jiang Xun?

11
00:01:35,599 --> 00:01:36,640
The doctor said she's fine.

12
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,439
and went home.

13
00:01:38,079 --> 00:01:39,400
That's all?

14
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,280
That's all.

15
00:01:41,599 --> 00:01:42,400
Feng,

16
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:43,799
I trust her.

17
00:01:44,599 --> 00:01:46,480
Don't be emotional.

18
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:47,840
You need to use facts to reason.

19
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,159
The fact is she was with me at that time.

20
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:51,200
When Xue Li got into trouble,

21
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,120
I was with her.

22
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,879
I even took a picture of her at that time.

23
00:01:57,239 --> 00:01:59,239
The time on the photo can prove this.

24
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,599
I heard that you confessed your love to her.

25
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:06,200
What do you mean by that?

26
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,280
Look.

27
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:12,919
There are obvious puncture marks

28
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:14,639
on Xue Li's neck.

29
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:16,400
There are signs of a fight at the scene.

30
00:02:16,639 --> 00:02:18,560
It's obvious that she was killed

31
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,080
to silence her after the deal failed.

32
00:02:20,879 --> 00:02:23,599
The museum was closed that day.

33
00:02:23,599 --> 00:02:25,439
There weren't many staff who could get in.

34
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,280
The ones who are familiar with the museum

35
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,080
and have access to it are even fewer.

36
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:35,159
Who do you think is the most suspicious?

37
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,479
The curator manager,

38
00:02:37,639 --> 00:02:38,680
Ke Yu'ang.

39
00:02:41,639 --> 00:02:42,560
Right, Shen.

40
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,919
According to Wei Chuan,

41
00:02:43,919 --> 00:02:45,479
when you entered the alley,

42
00:02:45,479 --> 00:02:47,120
Ke Yu'ang had already left the museum.

43
00:02:47,199 --> 00:02:49,120
So it was set up before he left.

44
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:52,879
Here's the situation.

45
00:02:54,199 --> 00:02:55,520
Jiaotu No.1 is missing,

46
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,000
and Xue Li is dead.

47
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,919
We need to search the entire museum.

48
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:02,080
Jiang Xun is the first witness.

49
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,039
She's the most suspicious.

50
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:04,240
Keep an eye on her.

51
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,919
She just came to me.

52
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:07,120
I'll keep an eye on her.

53
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,520
You and Wei Chuan keep an eye on them.

54
00:03:10,919 --> 00:03:11,479
Okay.

55
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,879
Next is Ke Yu'ang

56
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:17,240
and other staff.

57
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,840
You must remember

58
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:19,919
to investigate carefully.

59
00:03:19,919 --> 00:03:21,240
Don't miss any detail.

60
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,439
Got it?

61
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:23,400
Roger that.

62
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,479
Work.

63
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,039
Coming.

64
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,400
Hello, auntie.

65
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:44,560
Shen Yu.

66
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,719
Yes.

67
00:03:46,159 --> 00:03:47,960
You rushed off yesterday

68
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,479
after dropping Xun home.

69
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:50,960
I didn't even get to talk to you.

70
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,360
How's your dad?

71
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,840
He's doing well.

72
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,520
How about you?

73
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,919
I'm fine.

74
00:03:57,919 --> 00:03:59,319
How's work treating you?

75
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:01,319
It's going smoothly.

76
00:04:01,319 --> 00:04:02,280
I brought you a gift.

77
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:03,879
Have you eaten yet?

78
00:04:03,879 --> 00:04:04,680
I'm not hungry.

79
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,280
It's okay, ma'am.

80
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,319
Is Jiang Xun in the room?

81
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,080
Yes,

82
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:07,599
he's in the room,

83
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:08,159
reading.

84
00:04:08,159 --> 00:04:09,159
Reading.

85
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,800
He really loves studying.

86
00:04:27,639 --> 00:04:28,680
I scared you.

87
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,959
Are you feeling better?

88
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,879
Not really.

89
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,040
I'm a bit scared.

90
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,399
I'm a bit scared too.

91
00:04:41,319 --> 00:04:42,920
What? Trying to comfort me?

92
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,519
Who can handle

93
00:04:44,519 --> 00:04:45,480
finding a body in a dark passage?

94
00:04:46,399 --> 00:04:47,199
My heart

95
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,680
is still racing.

96
00:04:57,279 --> 00:04:58,079
Shen Shutu,

97
00:04:58,959 --> 00:05:00,160
I didn't kill anyone.

98
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,079
It's just a dream.

99
00:05:06,439 --> 00:05:07,240
Jiang Xun,

100
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,720
I believe you.

101
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,120
I want you

102
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,360
to trust me.

103
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,759
I've been wearing

104
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,040
this jade pendant since I was a child.

105
00:05:25,439 --> 00:05:26,920
It has become

106
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:28,360
a part of me.

107
00:05:38,959 --> 00:05:40,240
It means a lot to you.

108
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,160
I can't take it.

109
00:05:41,639 --> 00:05:43,399
It originally belonged to your ancestor.

110
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,800
So it should be returned to you.

111
00:05:46,319 --> 00:05:49,040
And I'm very relieved that

112
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,480
you value cultural relics.

113
00:05:50,959 --> 00:05:52,199
You will cherish it.

114
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,120
You gave me the pendant

115
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,560
to show your trust.

116
00:06:00,079 --> 00:06:01,399
I should be honest with you.

117
00:06:02,639 --> 00:06:03,680
Indeed,

118
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,839
I've been hiding something from you.

119
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,720
Can you

120
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,759
come to the museum tomorrow?

121
00:06:09,319 --> 00:06:10,360
Okay.

122
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,160
I won't bother you anymore.

123
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,120
I'm leaving.

124
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,560
Come here often, Shen.

125
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,120
Okay.

126
00:06:22,279 --> 00:06:23,399
Take care.

127
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:26,839
Hello, senior.

128
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,160
I'm at home.

129
00:06:30,639 --> 00:06:31,519
Okay.

130
00:06:33,319 --> 00:06:34,360
My senior called.

131
00:06:52,079 --> 00:06:53,000
Who are you?

132
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,480
Hello, I'm Jiang Xun's senior.

133
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,399
I'm here to see her.

134
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:58,120
You're looking for Xunxun?

135
00:06:59,439 --> 00:07:00,519
Come in.

136
00:07:02,079 --> 00:07:04,439
Xunxun, your senior is here to see you.

137
00:07:10,079 --> 00:07:13,120
Xunxun, sorry for scaring you yesterday.

138
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,319
I brought you some snacks.

139
00:07:14,839 --> 00:07:15,839
Thank you, senior.

140
00:07:16,759 --> 00:07:18,040
Yesterday,

141
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:20,560
how did you find that corridor?

142
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,240
Who is that person inside?

143
00:07:24,759 --> 00:07:26,519
I stumbled upon it by accident.

144
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:28,759
It was pitch dark inside.

145
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:30,680
I didn't see clearly.

146
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,720
That corridor was really, really long.

147
00:07:32,839 --> 00:07:35,240
I ran for a long time and still couldn't get out.

148
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,759
It was too scary.

149
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,399
It's okay.

150
00:07:39,399 --> 00:07:42,160
You should rest well today.

151
00:07:50,639 --> 00:07:53,079
Master, Ke Yu'ang is out.

152
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,399
I see him.

153
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:08,279
I'll go around from the left.

154
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:10,040
Keep a safe distance.

155
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,639
Master is going to see his wife.

156
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,839
What does it have to do with Ke Yu'ang?

157
00:08:31,639 --> 00:08:33,159
He obviously wants to compete with you.

158
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:35,080
He has a deep hostility towards me now.

159
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,360
Not just because of Jiang Xun.

160
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,440
Maybe he has sensed

161
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,399
that we are watching him.

162
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,120
The Cultural Relics Group

163
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,960
will be wrapping up soon and heading back to Hong Kong.

164
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:45,360
You, keep an eye on him.

165
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,320
If he's taken the Jiaotu No.1,

166
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,519
how would he get it out?

167
00:08:52,639 --> 00:08:55,320
Ke Yu'ang's team handles cultural relics exhibitions.

168
00:08:55,399 --> 00:08:56,360
If

169
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,120
they want to smuggle the chip out,

170
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,080
they'd likely use the same methods for relics.

171
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,279
So I suspect

172
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:03,720
they would mix the chip

173
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:05,120
with the artifacts

174
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,200
and smuggle it out of the country.

175
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,320
What should we do now?

176
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:12,919
Let Feifei keep an eye on Ke Yu'ang.

177
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:16,559
We'll check out the museum.

178
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:19,759
If it comes to a search and seizure,

179
00:09:19,759 --> 00:09:22,440
we'll request a joint operation with customs

180
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:25,720
to conduct a secondary inspection

181
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,120
on the artifacts.

182
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,960
But this process is very tedious

183
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,000
and requires a complete evidence chain.

184
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:33,759
I'll organize it, Master.

185
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,360
If we catch Ke Yu'ang,

186
00:09:35,559 --> 00:09:36,840
remember to give me a long vacation.

187
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,240
Alright, your vacation is approved.

188
00:09:44,159 --> 00:09:46,679
The current approach is fine,

189
00:09:47,679 --> 00:09:48,919
but I always feel

190
00:09:50,879 --> 00:09:52,440
something is still off.

191
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:54,480
I know what's wrong.

192
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:01,559
My future mother-in-law is in the Cultural Relics Group,

193
00:10:01,679 --> 00:10:03,159
with Ke Yu'ang in the relics team,

194
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,440
suspected of being an accomplice.

195
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,480
But you keep defending her

196
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,720
in front of Feng.

197
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:12,080
You're also wondering

198
00:10:12,759 --> 00:10:16,240
how she knew about that corridor.

199
00:10:17,639 --> 00:10:18,919
What are you talking about?

200
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,679
She's very sincere to me now,

201
00:10:20,679 --> 00:10:22,320
even invited me to a frank talk tomorrow.

202
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,279
Don't talk nonsense.

203
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:26,080
Fine.

204
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:34,440
Article 28 of the Law on Guarding State Secrets

205
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,240
stipulates that

206
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,120
any organization or individual

207
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,159
shall not illegally obtain or hold

208
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:41,559
state secret carriers.

209
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,320
Without the approval of the relevant authorities,

210
00:11:44,679 --> 00:11:48,080
No state secret carriers abroad.

211
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:51,519
In this case, the cultural relics exhibition process is proper,

212
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:53,200
and customs clearance procedures are complete.

213
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,960
Foreign spies may take this opportunity

214
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,279
to hide the illegally obtained Jiaotu No.1

215
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:00,879
within legally transported cultural relics

216
00:12:00,879 --> 00:12:01,879
and smuggle it out of the country,

217
00:12:01,879 --> 00:12:03,080
getting through customs.

218
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:06,600
Be vigilant against those who attempt to smuggle in secret.
